See the position deeper and properly evaluate if the position is good for you. }
1. Rg5! { Patient costing weaknesses so that the invade along the 7th rank can be stronger. No need to take the pawn on c5 } (1. Rdxc5 { [%csl Gf2,Gg3,Gh2] } 1... Rxc5 2. Rxc5 { [%cal Gh8g8] }) 1... g6 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gg7g6] } (1... Rg8 2. Rcxc5 Rxc5 3. Rxc5 Ra8 4. a4 { [%csl Gc7,Ga4,Ga5][%cal Gc5c7] }) 2. Re5! Rc3 3. Ree7 { [%csl Gc5] } 3... Rxa3 4. Rxh7+ Kg8 5. Rcg7+ Kf8 6. Rxg6 Re8 7. Rc6 Kg8 8. Rhc7 { [%cal Gc7c4,Gc7a7,Gc6a6] } *


