{ Control the seventh rank as part of a complex strategy.
When black has no counter-play, try to play slowly. } { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gb4b5,Gh5g6] }
1. Qa1! { [%cal Gg8f8,Ga1a3] } 1... Rb8 2. Qa3 { Important to identify that the breakthrough on Kingside does not work because there is Be8 stuff. And if the breakthrough is on kingside, white's d3 bishop cannot join the attack.
d3 bishop is strong on a-file. } { [%csl Gg8] } 2... Rbg8? (2... Ra8 3. Kg3!? { just wait and play useful oves } 3... Rab8 4. b5 axb5 5. h6+ Kf8 6. axb5 Qd8 7. Ra1 Ke7 8. b6 Ra8 9. Qb2 Rxa1 10. Qxa1 { a-file still belongs to white. }) 3. b5 axb5 4. h6+ { [%csl Gg8] } 4... Kf8 5. axb5 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gc6b5,Gc5c6,Ga3f8] } 5... Ke7 6. b6! { Just as the model. } { [%csl Gb7] } 6... Qb8 { [%csl Gb6,Gb7] } 7. Ra1 { [%csl Ga8][%cal Gb8a8,Ga3a7] } 7... Rc8 8. Qb4 { [%csl Gb8] } 8... Rhd8 9. Ra7 Kf8 10. Rh1 Be8 11. Rha1 Kg8 12. R1a4 Kf8 13. Qa3 { [%csl Ga8][%cal Ga3a8] } 13... Kg8 14. Kg3 Bd7 15. Kh4 Kh8 16. Qa1 Kg8 17. Kg3 Kf8 18. Kg2 Be8 { [%csl Gf3] } 19. Nd2 Bd7 20. Nb3 { [%csl Gb7] } 20... Re8 21. Na5 Nd8 22. Ba6 { [%csl Gd7] } 22... bxa6 23. Rxd7 Re7 24. Rxd8+ Rxd8 25. Nxc6 { Decide which file you are about to open by analyzing after opening the file, if our piece will be strong enough.
Also play slow enough when your opponent does not have counter-play. } *


