{ Central advantage: pawn on d5 and e4, training everything except the dark square bishop. Step-by-step achieving the position that we like. Consolidating move is important but play it only when our opponent has no counterplay.

This is how you force our opponent to play in a bad position. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Be3 c5 8. Qd2 O-O 9. Nf3 Bg4 10. Ng5 cxd4 11. cxd4 Nc6 12. h3 Bd7 13. Rb1 Rc8 14. Nf3 Na5 15. Bd3 Be6 16. O-O Bc4 17. Rfd1 b5 18. Bg5 a6 19. Rbc1 Bxd3 20. Rxc8 Qxc8 21. Qxd3 Re8 { Exploit the advantage of the c-file with 13 steps. Karpov shows his technique
step 1: put the rook on the opened c-file } { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gc1c6] } 22. Rc1 Qb7 { Step 2: Create and outpost square on c6 by advancing the d-pawn } 23. d5 Nc4 { Step 3: Remove the obstruction on the c-file } (23... Rc8 24. Rxc8+ Qxc8 25. Bxe7) 24. Nd2 { [%cal Ge8c8,Gb5c4] } 24... Nxd2 { Step 4: Prevent black from creating his out post on the c-file } 25. Bxd2! (25. Qxd2?! b4! { Black blocks the c-file by creating an outpost } { [%csl Gc3][%cal Gg7c3] }) 25... Rc8 { Step 5: Seize control of the outpost square } 26. Rc6 Be5 { Now Rxc6 is a threat and white's rook can no longer invade through the 7th rank.
Step 6: Force the bishop to leave the perfect e5 square } { [%csl Gd2] } 27. Bc3! Bb8 { Step 7: Better the queen and put it on d4 in order to force black weakens its kingside and get closer to the battel field on queenside. } { [%csl Gc8][%cal Gd8d5,Gd5c5,Gc5c8] } (27... Bxc3 28. Qxc3 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gc3c7] } 28... Re8 29. Qc5) 28. Qd4! { mult-purpose move. Stops b5-b4, ready to go to c5, force to weaken black's kingside. } 28... f6 { Step 8 : Continually fight for c7 using the bishop. } { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gf7f6] } 29. Ba5 Bd6 { Step 9: Support the rook and strengthen the control along the c-file } 30. Qc3 Re8 { Step 10: Be patient. Black has no counter-play so just play some consolidating moves. This step is really important. } 31. a3! { Can't allow b5-b4 } 31... Kg7 32. g3 Be5 33. Qc5 h5 { Step 11: Trying to invade on c7 by trading the dark-square bishop. } 34. Bc7! { Play this move only when all our pieces are at best condition. } 34... Ba1 { Step 12: Spare the c7 square four the rook. } 35. Bf4! Qd7 { Step 13: Seize the 7th rank (And win the game) } 36. Rc7 Qd8 37. d6 g5 38. d7 Rf8 39. Bd2! { Heading for a5 } { [%csl Ga5][%cal Gd2a5] } 39... Be5 40. Rb7 { White can win easily with Qa7, Qxa6 and Ba5. } { [%csl Ga5,Gd8,Ge7,Ga6][%cal Gc5a7,Ga7a6,Gd2a5] } *


