{ 通过来回拉扯、进攻对面弱点、在对面数个弱点上反复揉捏,达到让对方子力处于消极未知的作用。
分析局面的时候,明确自己的优势有哪些。并且试着(通过改善子力位置)把他们合并起来。
分析:如果我要实行计划,我的每个子的best position在哪里? }
1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 (5. e3) 5... Nb4 6. Bc4 e6 7. O-O N8c6 8. d3 Nd4 (8... Be7 9. a3) 9. Nxd4 cxd4 10. Ne2 a6 11. Ng3 Bd6 12. f4 O-O 13. Qf3 Kh8 14. Bd2 f5 15. Rae1 Nc6 16. Re2 Qc7 17. exf5 exf5 { 1. strong c4 bishop, whit can thus try to form a kingside attack.
2. black's bad d4 pawn
3. e2 rook contras the open file.
Yet how can white combine those advantage all? Bd7 and Rae8 for black is coming. } { [%csl Gg8,Gh8,Gd4][%cal Gc4g8,Ge2e8] } 18. Nh1!! { knight goes to g5, suddenly white's kingside is in trouble when the knight comes to g5 } { [%cal Gf3h5] } (18. Qd5 { [%csl Gg8] } 18... Ne7 19. Qf3 Bd7 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gd7c6] }) 18... Bd7 (18... Na5 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc4d5] } 19. Bd5 (19. Bxa5 Qxa5 20. Nf2 { [%csl Gd2,Gf4] }) 19... Rb8 (19... Qc5 20. b4) 20. b4 Nc6 21. a3) 19. Nf2 Rae8 20. Rfe1 Rxe2 21. Rxe2 { [%csl Gc6,Gd4,Ge7][%cal Gc6d4] } 21... Nd8 (21... Re8 22. Rxe8+ Bxe8 23. Qd5! Ne7 24. Qxd4 { This shows how Nimzowitch is combining all those factors together. }) (21... Bb4! { [%csl Gd4] }) (21... Na5 { [%csl Gb7] }) 22. Nh3 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gh3g5,Gf3h5] } 22... Bc6 23. Qh5 { Combing kingside attack and controlling the e-file } { [%csl Ge6,Ge4,Ge3] } (23. Qf2 { [%csl Gd4] }) 23... g6 24. Qh4 Kg7 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ge2e7] } 25. Qf2! { How the queen manueovers to a square that attacks the d4 pawn by attacking kingside. } { [%csl Gg6,Ge8,Ge7,Gd3,Gd4][%cal Gg7g6,Ge1e8,Ge2e7] } 25... Bc5 { [%csl Ge7,Gc5][%cal Ge2e7] } 26. b4! { [%csl Gd4,Gc5,Ge7][%cal Gc5d6] } 26... Bb6 { Restrict black's pieces. The bishop is forced to a bad diagonal. } { [%csl Gc5,Gd6,Ge7] } 27. Qh4! { 反复横跳把黑象引走之后,再用住黑方局面的问题。 } { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ge2e7] } 27... Re8 28. Re5! { 上一个张洁的outpost就这么体现出来了。黑的黑格象不再a3-f8斜线了。 } { [%cal Gh4h6] } 28... Nf7 (28... Rxe5 29. fxe5 { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gh4h6] }) 29. Bxf7 Qxf7 30. Ng5 Qg8 31. Rxe8 Bxe8 { 虽然车1欢乐,但四黑方的子力都非常烂,这些洞随时用上。
One advantage flows into another } 32. Qe1! { [%csl Ge7,Ge5][%cal Gh4e1,Ge1e7] } 32... Bc6 33. Qe7+ Kh8 34. b5 (34. Nf7+ Kg7 35. Ne5+ Kh8 36. Nxc6 bxc6 37. Qe5+ Qg7 38. Qb8+ Qg8 39. Qxb6) 34... Qg7 35. Qxg7+ Kxg7 36. bxc6 { And finally 1-0 on move 46 } *


