{ Playing "Cat and Mouse" When our opponent do not have any chances, play slowly to push forward and give our opponent chances to make mistakes.
Convertation of advantage. The domination of open-file on the queenside can lead to the kingside attack because of our opponent's restricted pieces is just hard to defend the king. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. c4 c6 5. Qc2 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. Nc3 h6 8. Bf4 Nbd7 9. cxd5 cxd5?! 10. Bd3 a6 11. O-O b5?! 12. a4 b4 13. Na2 { [%cal Ga2c1,Gc1b3,Gb3c5] } 13... Ne8 14. Nc1 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Ga4a5] } 14... a5 15. Nb3 Ba6 16. Bxa6 Rxa6 17. Qd3 { clear approach to put the rook on the file instead of the queen } 17... Ra7 18. Rfc1 Nd6 { [%csl Gd6,Gf4] } 19. Bxd6!! Bxd6 20. Rc6 (20. Rc2) 20... Nb8 21. Rc2 Nd7 22. Rac1 Nb6 { [%csl Ga5,Gb3] } 23. Qb5 { [%csl Ga7] } 23... Nc4 24. Nfd2 Nxd2 25. Rxd2 Qa8 26. Rdc2 Rd8 27. Rc6 g6 { Now we have maximized our control along the c-file. Thus we switch our attention to the kingside. Since black has no counter-play, it is okay to play slowly } 28. g3 Kg7 29. Kf1 Kg8 30. h4 h5 31. R1c2! { [%csl Gc1] } 31... Kh7 (31... f5 { [%csl Ge6,Gg6] } 32. Nc5 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gc5d3,Gd3e5] } (32. Qb6)) 32. Ke1 Kg8 33. Kd1 Kh7 { [%csl Gb8,Gc6] } 34. Kc1 Kg8 35. Kb1 Kh7 36. Qe2 { play slowly without any risk, wait till my opponent make mistake like playing f7-f5, so that it makes our lives easier } 36... Qb7 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gg3g4] } 37. Rc1! { 之前一直忽略的棋!预防白的后到g4之后黑的强行Ra6换车 } { [%csl Ga6,Gc2,Gg4,Gc6][%cal Ga7a6,Gc6c2,Ge2g4,Gc1h1] } (37. g4 hxg4 38. Qxg4 Ra6 { [%csl Gc6] } 39. Rxa6 Qxa6 { [%csl Gf1,Gd3][%cal Ga6f1] }) 37... Kg7 38. Qb5! { Give chances for black to make mistakes. } 38... Qa8 (38... Qxb5 39. axb5 { white can win seasier } { [%cal Gb5b7] }) 39. f4! { Finally slowly start our attack } 39... Kh7 (39... f5 40. Nc5) 40. Qe2 Qb7 41. g4! hxg4 42. Qxg4 Qe7 (42... Ra6 43. R6c2) 43. h5 Qf6 44. Ka2 { [%csl Ga2,Gb3] } (44. Rh1 Qf5+) 44... Kg7 45. hxg6 Qxg6 46. Qh4 Be7 47. Qf2! Kf8 48. Nd2 Rb7 49. Nb3 { Cat and mouse. If Nf3 then b4-b3 } (49. Nf3 b3+) 49... Ra7 50. Qh2 Bf6 51. Rc8 Rd7 52. Nc5! b3+ 53. Kxb3 Rd6 54. f5 Rb6+ 55. Ka2 { 1-0 } { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gg6f5,Gc5d7] } *


