{ some ideas: Attack c5, open up by a3. How to combine those together? }
1. Qd1!! { Ready to take whole control of h-file } 1... Kd8 2. Qg1 { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gg1c5,Gh1h2,Gg1h1] } 2... Nb6 3. Rh2 Qe7 { by acting on the kingside and force black's queen to go to the queenside, then we start to attack on the queenside. } { [%csl Gf8][%cal Ge7f8] } 4. Nb3 { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gb3c5] } 4... Kc7 5. Kf3 { [%csl Gc5] } 5... Nd7 { Through the previous moves, black's king and queen changes places. Thus a2-a3 makes more sense here. Also, a6-a5 is impossible here } 6. a3! bxa3 7. Ra2! { Our main goal is literally a-file. h-file does not matter a lot } 7... Rh4 8. Rxa3 Rgh8 9. Rb1 Rb8 10. Qe1! { Another switch position of the queen } 10... Rxg4 11. Kxg4 Bc8 12. Qa5+ { 1-0
The point is changing direction of attack to force opponent's piece in a rather uncomfortable way. } *


