{ [%csl Ge4] }
1. Ng5 { The endgame with a pawn on h5 is winning for black.
Work on all the threats: queenside pawns, white's e pawn and trying to push the h-pawn } (1. Kd4? Nf8! { find every chance to get into the king's pawn endgame and determine if it is good } { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gf8e6] } 2. Ng5 Ne6+ 3. Nxe6 Kxe6 4. Ke3 (4. b3 { [%cal Gh5h2,Gd4g1,Ge6e4] }) 4... a4 5. Kf4 h4 6. Kg4 Ke5 7. Kxh4 Kxe4) 1... Ne5! (1... a4 2. Nf3 { [%csl Ge6,Ge5] }) 2. Kd4 (2. b3) 2... Kd6 3. Nh3 (3. b3 Nc6+ 4. Ke3 { [%cal Gg4f3] } 4... b5 5. Nf3 Ne5 (5... a4 6. bxa4 bxa4 7. Kd3 (7. Kf4 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gc6e5] } 7... Na5 8. Nd2 Kc5 9. e5)) 6. Nh4 { [%csl Gb3,Ga3] } 6... a4) 3... a4! { Fix b2 and stop b2-b4 so black's king can try to fight against the weakness. If white place the king on c2 then h pawn will be pushed forward } 4. Nf4 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gh7h2] } 4... h4 5. Nh3 { [%csl Gc5] } 5... b6! { He wish that when Nc6 is played, the knight is on h3 instead of f4 } { [%csl Gc6,Gh3,Gf4][%cal Ge5c6] } (5... b5 6. Nf4 Nc6+ 7. Kc3! Ke5 8. Ng6+!) 6. Nf4 b5 7. Nh3 Nc6+ { [%csl Gh3] } 8. Ke3 (8. Kc3 Ke5 9. Kd3) 8... Kc5 { [%csl Gc5,Ge6][%cal Gd6c5,Gh3f4,Ge4d3,Gf4e6] } 9. Kd3 b4 { The point is the perfect square for the c6 knight, stopping e5 and supporting the queenside pawns. } 10. axb4+ Kxb4 { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gb4b2] } 11. Kc2 Nd4+ 12. Kb1 Ne6! { restrain, blockade, destroy the passed pawn } { [%cal Gd4e6,Ga4f4] } 13. Ka2 Kc4 14. Ka3 Kd4! 15. Kxa4 Kxe4 16. b4 { [%csl Gf3][%cal Ge6f4] } 16... Kf3 17. b5 Kg2 { 0-1 } { [%csl Gb6,Gh3] } 18. Nf4+ (18. Ng5 Nxg5 19. b6 Ne4) 18... Nxf4 19. b6 Nd5 20. b7 Nb6+ { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gb6d7] } *


