1. Nc4 { ties down opponent's pieces by attacking weaknesses } 1... Nc6 { [%csl Ga3][%cal Ga2a3] } 2. Kf3 Ke6 3. Ke3 Kd5 4. a3! { The secondary value of a side pawn:
1. ensures the d3 square for white's king
2. tactically prevent Kc5 by Nxa5
3. prevents a5-a4 } 4... Ke6 5. Kd3 Kd5 { Ne3 and Kc4 wants to be played, but now Nc4 will lead to Kc5. So black is trying to use zugzwang to force black's king to retreat to e6 } 6. f3 { Use zugzwang to force black to weaken its kingside pawns } 6... h6 7. Kc3 h5 8. Kd3 f6 9. f4! g5 { [%csl Gf5] } 10. Ne3+ Ke6 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Ge6f5] } 11. h4 { Stop black from using the 4-3 majority. } { [%csl Gg5,Gf5,Gf6] } (11. Kc4 { [%csl Gh4] }) 11... gxh4 12. gxh4 Ne7 13. Kc4 Ng6 14. Ng2! { The knight holds the position } { [%csl Gg2] } 14... Kd6 15. Kb5! Kd5 16. Kxa5 Ke4 17. b4 Kf3 18. b5! { black's knight cannot deal with the passed b-pawn so well } 18... Kxg2 19. b6 Nf8 20. Kb5 Nd7 21. a4 Nxb6 22. Kxb6 Kf3 23. a5 Kxf4 24. a6 Ke3 25. a7 f4 26. a8=Q f3 27. Qe8+ { 1-0 } *


