1. Rc1 { [%csl Ge5,Ga7] } 1... Nxe5 2. Nxa7 Bf6 3. b3! g5 4. Rc8+! { Queenside pawn majority is more useful in slight pieces endgames } 4... Rxc8 5. Nxc8 b5 { [%cal Ga3a6] } 6. Nd6 b4 7. a4! { 1. knight is bed at defending side pawn
2. stop bishop from getting to e7-b4
3. White wants the pawn to be as far away from black's king } (7. axb4 Be7 8. Bc5 Nd3 9. Kf3) 7... Nc6 { [%cal Gd6b7] } 8. Nb7 g4 9. a5 Nb8 10. Kf1 Kf8 11. Nc5 Nc6 12. a6 { 1-0
Rook's line pass pawn. Supporting it with a knight and a bishop. } *


