{ Threatening and preparing pawn breaks to distract opponent's pieces attention and try to attack on the other wing. }
1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 c6 6. e3 Qa5 7. Bxf6 Nxf6 8. a3 Ne4 9. Qb3 Be7 10. Bd3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 dxc4 12. Bxc4 Bf6 13. O-O O-O 14. e4 e5 15. d5 Qc7 16. Bd3 b6 17. c4 Bb7 18. Rfc1 Be7 19. Rc2 Bc5 20. Qb2 { black should play Rae8, ready for f5. Once white managed to stop this plan, then after some pieces are fixed on kingside, black can open up lines for his rooks and quickly shift his attention to queen side. } { [%csl Gf6,Gg2,Gg1,Gb5][%cal Gf8f6,Gb2g2,Ga1g1,Gb6b5] } 20... f6 { [%csl Ga4,Ga5] } (20... Rae8) 21. Rb1 Rad8 { [%cal Ga3a4] } 22. a4 Ba6 { [%csl Gd3,Gc2,Gb2,Gb4,Gc4,Ga4] } 23. Rd1 Rfe8 24. Qb3 Rd6 25. Nh4 g6 26. Be2 cxd5 27. exd5 e4 28. g3 e3 29. f4 { [%csl Gb3,Gf3] } 29... Bc8 30. Nf3 Bf5 31. Rb2 Re4 32. Kg2 Qc8 33. Ng1 g5 34. fxg5 fxg5 35. Rf1 g4 36. Bd3 Rf6 37. Ne2 Qf8 38. Rbb1 (38. Nf4 Qh6 39. Qc2 e2 40. Nxe2 Qh3+ 41. Kh1 Qxf1+) 38... Qh6 39. Qc2 Qh3+ 40. Kh1 Rxc4 41. Qxc4 Bxd3 42. Rxf6 Bxc4 43. Nf4 e2 44. Rg1 Qf1 *


