1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 Na5 9. Bc2 c5 10. d4 Qc7 11. Nbd2 Nc6 12. Nf1 cxd4 13. cxd4 Bg4 14. d5 Nd4 15. Bd3 O-O 16. Be3 Rac8 17. Bxd4 exd4 18. a4 Qb6 19. axb5 axb5 20. h3 Bxf3 21. Qxf3 Nd7 22. Rec1 Nc5 23. b4! Na4 (23... Nxd3 24. Qxd3 { [%csl Gc3][%cal Gf1d2,Gd2b3,Gb3a5,Ga5c6,Ga1a5,Gc8c3] }) 24. Rxc8 Rxc8 25. e5!! { Changes the focus of the game from queenside to kingside. Previously you may think that knight is strong on a4 and the rook is strong on c4, however now when the focus of position is shifted to kingside, white's rook seems can be good on e1 and knight and queen will cooperate well on the kingside. } 25... g6 (25... dxe5 26. Qf5) 26. e6 Rf8 27. Ng3! Qb7? { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gf7f5] } (27... fxe6 28. Qg4 Kg7 (28... e5 29. Bxg6 hxg6 30. Qxg6+ Kh8 31. Nh5 Rg8 32. Qh6#) 29. dxe6) (27... Qc7! 28. Bxb5) 28. Nf5! { [%cal Gf7e6] } 28... fxe6 29. dxe6 Qc7 { [%csl Ge7,Gf3,Ge4,Gd5,Gc6,Gb7,Ga8] } (29... Qxf3 30. Nxe7+) 30. Qc6! Qd8 31. Nxe7+ Qxe7 32. Bxb5 Nc3 33. Qd7 Qxd7 34. Bxd7 Rb8 35. e7 Kf7 36. Re1 Re8 37. Bxe8+ Kxe8 38. Re6 d5 39. Kf1 Nb5 40. Ke2 Nc7 41. Re5 Na6 42. b5 Nb4 43. b6 d3+ 44. Kd2 Kd7 45. e8=Q+ Kd6 46. Qe7+ Kc6 47. Qxb4 *


