{ When one pawn break is stopped, find the chances around. }
1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 Nd7 4. Nc3 Ngf6 5. Bg5 Bb4 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Qa4 Bxc3+ (7... c5) 8. bxc3 O-O 9. e3 c5 10. Bd3 c4 11. Bc2 Qe7 12. O-O a6 { e2-e4 is the idea } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Ge3e4] } 13. Rfe1 Qe6 14. Nd2 { black's counter-idea: protect c4 and play Ne4 stop e3-e4 at all cost } 14... b5 15. Qa5 Ne4 { [%csl Gb5,Ga6] } 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. a4! { by playing b5, black's queenside pawn chain is weakened } 17... Qd5 (17... bxa4 { [%csl Gc4,Ga4] } 18. Reb1 { [%csl Gc4,Ga4] }) 18. axb5 Qxg5 19. Bxe4 Rb8 20. bxa6 Rb5 21. Qc7 Nb6 22. a7 Bh3 23. Reb1! { Be patient, no need to queen immediately to get more than a knight. } 23... Rxb1+ 24. Rxb1 f5 25. Bf3 f4 26. exf4 { 1-0 } *


