{ Strategic plan, breakthrough passive defense
trade queens
important f5 breakthrough
open of files (b2 pawn victim)
trade pieces }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Bd3 Bxd3 5. Qxd3 e6 6. Ne2 Qb6 { [%csl Ge5,Gc5,Gf4][%cal Gc6c5,Gf2f4] } 7. O-O Qa6! 8. Qd1 c5 9. c3 (9. Nd2) 9... Nc6 10. Nd2 cxd4 (10... Nxd4) 11. cxd4 Qd3 12. Nb3 Qxd1 13. Rxd1 { white rook is on the wrong square for supporting the plan of f4-f5 } 13... Nge7 14. Bd2 a5 15. Rac1 b6! { block white's d2 bishop and b3 knight } { [%csl Gd2,Gc6,Gc5,Gf5][%cal Gf2f5] } 16. a4 Kd7 17. Nc3 Na7 18. Kf1 Nec6 19. Ke2 Rc8 20. Be1 Be7 21. Nb1 { [%csl Gd4] } 21... f5! { if white ignores, g5 and h5 will be pushed. if ef, d4 is in trouble and white has to admit that he will be forced to defend for the rest of the game } 22. exf6 Bxf6 { [%csl Gd4] } 23. Bc3 Nb4 24. Bd2 Nac6 25. Be3 Na2! 26. Rc2 Rc7 27. Na3 Rhc8 { how to exploit active pieces } { [%csl Gc8,Gc7,Gh4,Gg4] } 28. Rcd2 Na7 29. Rd3 Nb4 30. R3d2 { [%cal Gc8c2] } 30... Rc6 31. Rb1 Be7 32. Ra1 Bd6 33. h3 R8c7 34. Rad1 Na2 35. Ra1 Bxa3 36. Rxa2 Bb4 37. Rd1 Rc4 38. Rc1 Nc6 39. Rxc4? dxc4 40. Nd2 Bxd2! { Eliminate the only piece that can fight against his plan to put the king on d5 } 41. Kxd2 Kd6 42. Kc3 Kd5 43. Ra1 g6! { no hurry. Place the pawns on light suqare } 44. f3 Rb7 45. Ra3 b5! { break through the b-file and the victim of b2 pawn } 46. axb5 Rxb5 47. Bf2 Nb4 48. b3 (48. Bg1 Nd3 49. b3 cxb3 50. Rxb3 Rxb3+ 51. Kxb3 Ne1) 48... cxb3 49. Kxb3 Nc6+ 50. Kc3 Rb1 { 1. Invasion of rook
2. weakened d4 pawn
3. strong a4 passed pawn
4. Advantage in knight-bishop endgame } 51. Ra4 Rc1+ 52. Kd2 Rc4! 53. Ra1 a4 54. Ra3 Na7! 55. Ra1 Nb5 56. Rb1 Kc6 { Nxd4 liberates white's pieces } 57. Kd3 Rc3+ 58. Kd2 Rb3! 59. Rc1+ Kb7 60. Rc2 a3 61. Bg3 Nxd4 62. Rc7+ Kb6 63. Rc4 Kb5 64. Rc8 Nc6 65. Ra8 Rb2+ 66. Ke3 Rxg2 67. Bf2 Nb4! { 1-0 } *


