{ strategic ideas
against the idea
pawn structure
rook invasion along the 4th rank }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Bd3 Bxd3 5. Qxd3 e6 6. Nc3 Qb6 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gf2f5] } 7. Nge2 c5 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. O-O Ne7 10. Na4 Qc6 11. Nxc5 Qxc5 12. Be3 Qc7 13. f4 Nf5 14. c3 Nc6 15. Rad1 (15. Rae1 g6 16. g4 { black exploits the fact that white's position is full of holes } (16. Bf2 h5 17. g3 { and h3, g4 } { [%csl Gh3,Gg4] }) 16... Nxe3 17. Qxe3 h5! { Tactical refutation to stop white's plan } 18. g5 (18. h3 hxg4 19. hxg4 g5 (19... O-O-O)) 18... O-O! { Now white's kingside pawns have lost the mobilbility } 19. Nd4 Qb6 20. Rf2 Rfc8 21. a3 Rc7) 15... g6 16. g4 Nxe3 17. Qxe3 h5! 18. g5 { [%cal Gh8c8,Gc8c3,Ga8c8] } 18... O-O 19. Nd4 Qb6 { [%csl Gf6,Ge5,Gf4,Gg5] } 20. Rf2 { This should be Rac8 } 20... Rfc8 21. Rd3 Na5?! { Capablanca sensed this plan was not always good } { [%csl Ge5,Gf4,Gg5] } 22. Re2 Re8! { Strong prevention! Black sensed that white's kingside attack has not yet exhausted by Qh3 Ne6 etc } { [%csl Ge6][%cal Ge3h3,Gd4e6] } 23. Kg2 Nc6 { Admit the mistake } 24. Red2 (24. Nxc6 Qxc6 25. Rd4) 24... Rec8 { because white's rook has left the e-file } 25. Re2 Ne7! { prevents the f5 idea and Nxc6 } 26. Red2 Rc4 27. Qh3 { Dubious idea to stop Nf5 } 27... Kg7! { Continue the plan of Nf5 } { [%csl Gf5][%cal Ge7f5] } 28. Rf2 a5 29. Re2 Nf5 30. Nxf5+ gxf5 31. Qf3 Kg6 { Now e4 square is available for the rook } 32. Red2 Re4 33. Rd4 Rc8 34. a3 Rc4 35. Qf2 Qb5 36. Kg3 Rcxd4 37. cxd4 Qc4 38. Kg2 b5 39. Kg1 b4 40. axb4 axb4 41. Kg2 Qc1 42. Kg3 Qh1 43. Rd3 Re1 44. Rf3 Rd1 45. b3 Rc1 46. Re3 Rf1 { 0-1 } *


