{ Preparations: after pawn break, not allowing opponent's pieces to be active
threatens pawn break on one side, once opponent's pieces are attracted to defend against, open up the other side.
put the pawnn beside the most advanced pawn
e5-d4 structure. Nimzo's idea etc
war of two sides, readying for g4-f5 quickly
black is quicker to play c5 so quicker dominate c-file. then b5-b4 break. f5 idea to pressure f6.
Evaluate the weakness between e6 and d4. When black's bishop can go on f6 on endgame to attack d4 and tie white's rook down, e6 weakness is not that weak in contrastion. }
