{ A complete plan against high weak pawns }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 Na5 9. Bc2 c5 10. d4 Qc7 11. Nbd2 O-O 12. h3 Nc6 13. d5 Nd8 14. a4 b4 15. Nc4 a5 { [%csl Ge5,Gd6] } 16. Nfxe5 Ba6 17. Bb3 dxe5 18. d6 Bxd6 19. Qxd6 (19. Nxd6 c4) 19... Qxd6 20. Nxd6 Nb7 21. Nxb7 Bxb7 22. cxb4 cxb4 23. f3 { [%csl Gf3,Ge4,Gh2][%cal Gc8b7,Gb7h1] } 23... Rfd8 24. Be3 { [%csl Gd3,Gc4] } 24... h6 25. Red1 Bc6 26. Rac1 Be8 27. Kf2 Rxd1 28. Rxd1 Rc8 { Important position } { [%csl Gg4] } 29. g4 { If Bb6, then Nd7 - c5 idea is strong. The idea of g4 is to play h4-g5 and play Bb6 without Nd7. If Nd7, then Rd5 } (29. Bb6? Nd7 30. Bxa5 Nc5) 29... Bd7 { [%csl Ga5,Gb4] } (29... Rb8 30. Rc1 Nd7 31. Rc7 Nf8 32. Rc5 Ra8 33. Bd5 { [%csl Ga5] }) (29... Kf8 30. h4 Nd7 31. Rd5! { [%csl Ga5,Gf5,Ge5][%cal Gd5a5] }) 30. Bb6 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gf6d7] } 30... Be6 31. Bxe6 fxe6 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Gb6a5] } 32. Rd8+! Rxd8 33. Bxd8 Nd7 34. Bxa5 Nc5 35. b3! Nxb3 36. Bxb4 Nd4 37. a5 { 1-0 } *


